This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the 70th International Astronautical Congress. Pence discusses the United States' renewed commitment to space exploration under President Donald Trump's leadership. He highlights the goal of returning American astronauts to the Moon by 2024 and establishing a foundation for an eventual mission to Mars. Pence also emphasizes the importance of cooperation among freedom-loving nations in advancing space exploration and ensuring the responsible use of resources found in outer space. He announces the creation of the United States Space Force, which will be dedicated to defending the nation's interests in space. Pence concludes by expressing confidence that with the support of international allies and God's help, the United States will lead the world into the vast expanse of space once again.